}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "P/N:FK1HU2011812 2007/04/13" and "USB2.0 7Port HUB 1.8" is silkscreened on the top of the board. :This hub looks near identical in form-factor and markings to the [[D-Link DUB-H7 rev A2]] / [[D-Link DUB-H7 rev A5]]. The silkscreened text also matches up (in contents, font, and location). A sticker with "UH7U(1.8)" and "S/N:0707PH006715" printed on it is affixed to the bottom of the board. Googlery indicates that the manufacturer of the device is the Taiwan based [http://www.mct.com.tw '''Magic Control Technology Corp.''' ('''MCT''')]. Additional confirmation comes from [ftp://ftp.dlink.es/Usb/USB2.0%20&%20FireWire/DUB-H7/Confidencial/DUB-H7%20ver%20A2%20RoHS%20test%20report.pdf this DUB-H7 Chemical Analysis Report]..
The '''NXP''' hub IC package is marked with "NXP", "ISP1521BE, "CH0549 02", and "TPD0712C".
The S/N of the unit populating this entry is '''07PH-06542'''.
The power adapter included with this unit is a '''Fairway Electronic''' WN20U-050 (100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 1.0A max -> 5VDC 3.0A).
